<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
These sentence patterns mean to copy exactly in words or actions whatever V describes.
</p>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
The dictionary form is used before @HI{{@EM{{toorini}}}} when the action is going to be performed from now.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}gayaru@EM{{toorini}},yattekudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please do as I do.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
The @Vta{{}}-form is used before @HI{{@EM{{toorini}}}} when the action has already been performed.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{see}}ta@EM{{toorini}},@KJ{{tale}}shitekudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please tell us what you saw as it was.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
When @HI{{@EM{{notoori}}}} means "in the same manner", the @HI{{ni}} is optional. When it means an agreement of some sort (concordance),
the particle @HI{{ni}} cannot be used.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{think}}tta@EM{{toori}}@KJ{{he}}ga@FG{{@KJ{{one^turn^before}}:ichibansaki}}ni@KJ{{come}}teita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      As I expected, he was the first to come.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
The form @N{{}}@HI{{@EM{{notoorini}}}} means "in the same manner".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{line}}no@EM{{toorini}},@KJ{{paper}}wo@KJ{{cut}}ttekudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please cut the paper following the line.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
The suffix @HI{{doori}}, that is @N{{}}@HI{{@EM{{doori}}}} is more common than @N{{}}@HI{{@EM{{notoorini}}}}.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{finger^show}}:shiji}}@EM{{doori}}(ni)@KJ{{move}}ite@KJ{{below}}sai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please move as directed.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
If @HI{{@EM{{toori}}}} is followed by the object marker @HI{{wo}}, then it is equivalent to @HI{{@EM{{toori}}nokoto}}

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{think}}tteiru@EM{{toori}}(nokoto)wo@KJ{{write}}ite@KJ{{below}}sai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please write what you are thinking.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

